The paper focuses on the design and evaluation of a deep learning system for unconstrained face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs) also suggests a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses open issues related to DCNNs for face verification, which could also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
